04:06.660 --> 04:07.900
So I wanted to talk a second, I was like,

04:07.900 --> 04:11.080
how would you go about deploying this app?

04:11.120 --> 04:15.060
The first thing, so let's stop our server here,

04:16.240 --> 04:18.400
is we'd made an MPM run build.

04:18.400 --> 04:20.600
We already did that at the beginning of the course.

04:20.600 --> 04:23.900
This will build everything into a very nice,

04:23.900 --> 04:26.640
ready to go package here called dist.

04:26.640 --> 04:30.420
So you have index.html and all of your static assets.

04:32.120 --> 04:33.840
So that's cool.

04:33.840 --> 04:35.960
That's all ready to be deployed to a CDN.

04:36.800 --> 04:39.800
You would also have to deploy your API.

04:42.440 --> 04:45.400
So let's talk just a second about what you would do there.

04:47.080 --> 04:50.320
So this is the API.

04:53.320 --> 04:57.880
The first thing is, this is all running on SQLite,

04:57.880 --> 04:59.600
which there's another good course on Frontend Masters

04:59.600 --> 05:01.600
if you wanna learn about SQLite that I taught.

05:02.480 --> 05:07.160
So you either need to move this database off of the server

05:07.160 --> 05:09.280
or you just have to accept that it's going to

05:09.280 --> 05:11.200
not preserve your data long-term.

05:11.200 --> 05:12.040
One of those two things.

05:12.040 --> 05:14.360
Like if you don't care about saving your database,

05:14.360 --> 05:15.800
by all means, leave it just the way it is.

05:15.800 --> 05:19.320
If you care about saving your database,

05:19.320 --> 05:21.640
there's a cool database company called Neon.

05:21.640 --> 05:25.240
I don't know if you've heard of it, it's pretty cool.

05:25.240 --> 05:27.960
You could definitely load this SQLite database

05:27.960 --> 05:30.920
directly into Neon and then put the Neon connection string

05:30.920 --> 05:31.760
in here.

05:31.760 --> 05:36.320
I am 95% sure that this is just all very dumb SQL

05:36.320 --> 05:40.120
that would all work directly with Postgres.

05:40.120 --> 05:43.520
So you would just have to change from this SQLite driver

05:43.520 --> 05:45.720
to something like the Neon serverless driver

05:45.720 --> 05:46.640
or something like that.

05:46.640 --> 05:48.120
It would be pretty fast to convert this

05:48.120 --> 05:51.680
from SQLite to Postgres.

05:51.680 --> 05:53.280
Or you could use something like Turso,

05:53.280 --> 05:55.080
which does SQLite in the cloud.

05:55.080 --> 05:57.200
All of those are valid options.

05:57.200 --> 05:59.960
And then you'd have to deploy this to something like

05:59.960 --> 06:03.800
Vercel or Elastic Beanstalk or something like that.

06:05.400 --> 06:08.960
So if you're able to do that, deploy all your static assets,

06:08.960 --> 06:10.680
deploy your app, change your database

06:10.680 --> 06:13.320
if you care about changing your database,

06:13.320 --> 06:15.480
then everything should just work.

06:15.480 --> 06:16.600
Last thing you might need to move,

06:16.600 --> 06:19.080
you might need to move the style.css

06:19.080 --> 06:20.840
and some of the images over to this project

06:20.840 --> 06:22.600
because that's kind of where they belong.

06:22.600 --> 06:25.480
I was kind of cheating by making it available on the API

06:25.480 --> 06:26.640
so that you never had to worry about

06:26.640 --> 06:29.000
where the images of the styles were coming from,

06:29.000 --> 06:31.240
but that might be the case as well.

06:31.240 --> 06:32.240
Any questions?

